headline: Aon (AON) Earnings Beat Five-Year Average Yet Margin Dip Undercuts Bullish Sentiment
summary: Aon (AON) reported earnings that continue their steady climb, with EPS growth forecast at 12.02% per year and revenue expected to rise 5.1% annually. The company’s net profit margin landed at 16%, just shy of last year's 16.3%. Over the past five years, earnings have grown by 10.6% per year and registered 11.6% growth this past year, outperforming the longer-term average.
